The paper discusses a solution for authentication in group communication using IP multicast protocol. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network protocols (cs.NI). The paper also proposes an efficient design for the implementation of the protocol, which involves parallelism and cryptography algorithms, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), software engineering (cs.SE), and cryptography and security (cs.CY).
